Regards,  PharmEasy

notes.body:
Hi Team,

This is extremely concerning.

As discussed yesterday, every medicine bill must strictly match the
uploaded prescription. All three medicines are required to be billed in the
name of Girish Jamba, and only the Aqua Soft lotion should be billed under
Natasha Jamba.

However, you have issued a bill for Onabet SD lotion—a
prescription-mandatory medicine—in the name of a 4-year-old child (Natasha
Jamba) who has no prescription for it.
This is a major lapse, completely unacceptable, and raises serious
questions about the integrity and compliance standards of your platform.
Issuing prescription-only medication in the name of a minor without a valid
prescription is not just careless, it is illegal and reflects a severe
failure in your verification process.

In any dispute, the bill is the primary proof of transaction, and such
errors create unnecessary ambiguity and liability. I expect this to be
corrected immediately and proper action taken to ensure such violations do
not occur again.

Regards,
Girish

      Subject: Urgent Resolution Required for Non-Delivery of Medicine Order – Order ID: 656317517474824192  
      Description:  Dear PharmEasy Team,   
 I am writing to express my serious concern and disappointment regarding the handling of my recent order (Order ID: 656317517474824192). This issue is completely unacceptable, especially considering that the order contains medicines, not regular goods. 
   
 On 10th December, the delivery agent called me and asked me to come to Bihpur Chowk, which is around 3 km away from my home. When I refused, he assured me that the order would be delivered the next day, i.e., 11th December. However, I did not receive the order on that day. 
   
 I contacted Customer Support on 11th itself and was informed that a complaint had been registered. Today, 12th December, I received an “Out for Delivery” message, yet the order still has not been delivered. I called today to customer support but I didn't get any resolution. 
   
 This raises a serious question—what kind of service is this? Have I made a mistake by purchasing medicines from your platform? I need an immediate and proper resolution to this issue. Otherwise, I will be compelled to escalate this matter further, including sharing the experience on social media platforms. 
   
 I have been purchasing medicines from PharmEasy for the past five years, and I expect better service. Even last year, I had faced a similar issue and had to collect the package from your  courier office. This time, I will not tolerate such negligence. 
   
 Kindly treat this matter with the highest priority and provide a prompt resolution. 
   
 Regards, 
 Keshav Deo

Dear PharmEasy Team,

I am writing to express my serious concern and disappointment regarding the handling of my recent order (Order ID: 656317517474824192). This issue is completely unacceptable, especially considering that the order contains medicines, not regular goods.

On 10th December, the delivery agent called me and asked me to come to Bihpur Chowk, which is around 3 km away from my home. When I refused, he assured me that the order would be delivered the next day, i.e., 11th December. However, I did not receive the order on that day.

I contacted Customer Support on 11th itself and was informed that a complaint had been registered. Today, 12th December, I received an “Out for Delivery” message, yet the order still has not been delivered. I called today to customer support but I didn't get any resolution.

This raises a serious question—what kind of service is this? Have I made a mistake by purchasing medicines from your platform? I need an immediate and proper resolution to this issue. Otherwise, I will be compelled to escalate this matter further, including sharing the experience on social media platforms.

I have been purchasing medicines from PharmEasy for the past five years, and I expect better service. Even last year, I had faced a similar issue and had to collect the package from your  courier office. This time, I will not tolerate such negligence.

Kindly treat this matter with the highest priority and provide a prompt resolution.

Regards,
Keshav Deo

At this point, I request you to arrange a direct conversation with the

I expect a prompt and concrete resolution at the earliest.

Keshav Deo

I expect a prompt and concrete resolution at the earliest.

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Support Team,

I am writing to report a serious issue with my recent order. I had ordered 6 different types of medicines, but only 5 were delivered. One complete medicine type is missing from the package.

Medicines Ordered (All 6 types):

  1.  Atortrue 10mg - Qty: 2
  2.  Telkonol 20mg - Qty: 3
  3.  Ubicar - Qty: 3
  4.  Trajenta Duo 2.5/500mg - Qty: 6
  5.  Volix R 0.3/1mg - Qty: 6
  6.  Metbetic GI 2mg - Qty: 4

However, only 5 medicines were delivered, and one item from the above list is missing.

On the date of delivery, I was out of the city for a family function, and our tenant received the package. He did not open the delivery packet, and handed me the sealed, unopened box when I returned. Once I opened it, I found that one medicine type was missing.

This clearly shows that the order was not properly checked before dispatch, which is extremely disappointing.

I am raising this complaint so that the missing medicine can be sent to me immediately.

If this issue is not resolved, I will escalate it on social platforms along with the relevant government regulations regarding online medicine delivery.

Please look into this urgently and arrange the replacement.
Thank you,
Rahul

+919643042301(whatsapp only)

I am writing to report a serious issue with my recent order. I had ordered 6 different types of medicines, but only 5 were delivered. One complete medicine type is missing from the package.

Medicines Ordered (All 6 types):

  1.  Atortrue 10mg - Qty: 2
  2.  Telkonol 20mg - Qty: 3
  3.  Ubicar - Qty: 3
  4.  Trajenta Duo 2.5/500mg - Qty: 6
  5.  Volix R 0.3/1mg - Qty: 6
  6.  Metbetic GI 2mg - Qty: 4

However, only 5 medicines were delivered, and one item from the above list is missing.

On the date of delivery, I was out of the city for a family function, and our tenant received the package. He did not open the delivery packet, and handed me the sealed, unopened box when I returned. Once I opened it, I found that one medicine type was missing.

This clearly shows that the order was not properly checked before dispatch, which is extremely disappointing.

I am raising this complaint so that the missing medicine can be sent to me immediately.

If this issue is not resolved, I will escalate it on social platforms along with the relevant government regulations regarding online medicine delivery.

Please look into this urgently and arrange the replacement.
Thank you,
Rahul
